net.dv8tion.jda.core.managers

Class WebhookManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dv8tion.jda.core.managers.WebhookManager

  • public class WebhookManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Facade for a WebhookManagerUpdatable instance.
    Simplifies managing flow for convenience.

    This decoration allows to modify a single field by automatically building an update RestAction

      • setName

        public AuditableRestAction<java.lang.Void> setName(java.lang.String name)
        Sets the default name of the selected Webhook.
        Wraps WebhookManagerUpdatable.getNameField()

        A webhook name must not be null!

        Parameters:
        name - The new default name for the selected Webhook
        Returns:
        AuditableRestAction
        Update RestAction from #update()
        Throws:
        InsufficientPermissionException - If the currently logged in account does not have the Permission MANAGE_WEBHOOKS
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the provided name is null
        See Also:
        WebhookManagerUpdatable.getNameField(), WebhookManagerUpdatable.update()

      • setChannel

        public AuditableRestAction<java.lang.Void> setChannel(TextChannel channel)
        Sets the TextChannel of the selected Webhook.
        Wraps WebhookManagerUpdatable.getChannelField()

        A webhook channel must not be null and must be in the same Guild!

        Parameters:
        channel - The new TextChannel for the selected Webhook
        Returns:
        AuditableRestAction
        Update RestAction from #update()
        Throws:
        InsufficientPermissionException - If the currently logged in account does not have the Permission MANAGE_WEBHOOKS in either the current or the specified TextChannel
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the provided channel is null or from a different Guild
        See Also:
        WebhookManagerUpdatable.getChannelField(), WebhookManagerUpdatable.update()
